One answer that the industry has come up with is consolidation. In Refactor=
ing Restaurants [ https://substack.com/redirect/f165882b-bc12-4459-a05b-3b8=
702be21ee?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNp=
U ], Byrne Hobart wrote that:=C2=A0=C2=A0
Chain restaurants are 77% of total restaurant visits in the US [ https://su=
bstack.com/redirect/65bf7c33-dce4-42b5-a588-6381b55ce1af?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3=
QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], and have grown over tim=
e. And within the independent restaurant space, there's been consolidation =
at the backend, where the food distribution industry has consolidated throu=
